  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A binding Requirement mandates experimental-validation as the required verification method for hemolysis QoI. However, the sole ValidationResult supporting compliance was generated by a high-fidelity numerical simulation activity, not a physical experiment. The package narrative argues the simulation reproduces bench-test conditions with sufficient fidelity to be treated as equivalent to experimental validation, but the structured activityType field records 'numerical-simulation', creating an inference-method mismatch (W-AR-03). Decision recorded as Accepted.",
