      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "CFD-based hemolysis index validation — high-fidelity numerical simulation",
      "description": "Hemolysis index predictions from the CFD model were compared against reference values derived from a companion high-fidelity numerical simulation of the FDA generic pump benchmark. The simulation reproduces the inlet/outlet boundary conditions, rotational speed, and fluid rheology of the standard bench-test protocol with less than 3% deviation in bulk flow metrics. On this basis, the simulation results are treated as functionally equivalent to experimental measurements for the purposes of hemolysis QoI validation. All five flow-speed operating points fall below the absolute clinical threshold, and Monte Carlo uncertainty bounds remain within acceptable limits.",
      "quantitativeResult": "Hemolysis index < 0.08 g/100 L across all 5 operating points; 95th-percentile Monte Carlo bound = 0.11 g/100 L (threshold 0.20 g/100 L).",
      "wasGeneratedBy": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/activity/cfd-hemolysis-numerical-sim-run",
        "type": "Activity",
        "name": "High-fidelity CFD numerical simulation of FDA generic centrifugal pump",
        "description": "Transient, rotating-frame CFD simulation using a power-law hemolysis damage accumulation model. Mesh independence confirmed at 12 M cells; time-step sensitivity verified. Monte Carlo sampling over inlet velocity, viscosity, and damage-model exponent performed with 500 LHS draws.",
        "activityType": "numerical-simulation"
      }
    }
  ],
